                <h1>Why Do Background Checks Take 3 Weeks?</h1>
                <p>A background check can take up to three weeks due to various factors, including the complexity of the check and the responsiveness of different agencies. Delays may arise from verifying employment history, criminal records, and education. Expect thoroughness; the hiring process might be lengthy but ensures safety and integrity.</p>
